            <link>https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/as-cancer-rates-fall-nationally-iowa-sees-a-troubling-rise-in-diagnoses</link>
            <description><![CDATA[For years, national conversations about cancer have often focused on the so-called "Cancer Alley" in the Deep South or Appalachian states with high smoking rates. But recently, a different state has grabbed headlines. Iowa has the second-highest cancer incidence in the country and is one of only three states where rates are rising. Special correspondent Fred de Sam Lazaro reports.]]></description>
